               <msContents>
                  <summary>A copy of the <title>Bahār-i Dānish</title> (Spring of Wisdom) authored
                     by <persName key="person_17950016" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/17950016/">ʻInāyat
                        Allāh (d. ca. 1671)</persName> in 1061 AH (1651 CE) during the reign of
                        <persName>Shāh Jahān</persName>, relates the romantic adventures of Jahāndār
                     Sulṭān and Bahravar Bānū, which serves as a frame story interwoven with other
                     tales. One of six copies held in the Rylands, this redaction contains a preface
                     by the author's younger brother and pupil <persName key="person_270970434"
                        >Muḥammad Ṣāliḥ</persName> followed by the author's own introduction in
                     which he explains how he adapted the tale frome that he heard a young Brahmin
                     recite.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_919-item1">
                     <author key="person_17950016" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/17950016/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="standard">ʻInāyat Allāh, d. ca.
                           1671</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">‘Ināyat Allāh Kanbū
                           Lāhūrī</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Kanbū, ‘Ināyat
                        Allāh</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">عنايت الله</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="standard">عنايت الله كنبو لاهوری</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="alt">كنبو، عنايت الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1151">Bahār-i Dānish</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_1151">بهار دانش</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmala"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> فاتحه کتاب مستطاب افرینش و پیرایهٔ صحیفهٔ دانش و بینش حمد
                        خداوند خردبخش سخن آفرین و صورت نمای معنی ایجاد و تکوین است که بر لطایف ابداع
                        و صنایع اختراع قدرت کامله پس از ماهتاب... </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="226a" to="226a"> برگ ۲۲۶ر (folio 226a):</locus> سیه کاری مکن
                        چون خامهٔ خویش * بشو از چشم بر خون نامه‌ٔ خویش | زبان را گوشمالی خاموشی ده *
                        که هست از هرچه کوئی خاموشی به. </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="226a" to="226a"> برگ ۲۲۶ر (folio 226a):</locus> تمام شد کتاب
                        بهار دانش نصیف الفضلاء زمان مبان عنایت الله کنبوهی ساکن دار السلطنه لاهور
                        بتاریخ نهم ۹ ماه حنوری سنه ۱۸۹۰ عیسوی روز جمعه. </colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>S. H. Qasemi documents 244 manuscripts and printed editions of this work.
                        C. A. Storey also notes various manuscripts and translations into English,
                        German, French, Turkish, and Urdu. For other copies of this work held in the
                        Rylands, see <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6678"><idno>Persian
                              MS 88</idno></ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6678"><idno>Persian
                              MS 199</idno></ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6960">463</ref>,
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26591"
                           >991</ref>, and <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26536">1017</ref>.
                        For a glossary of terms found in this work entitled <title>Rang-i
                           Bahār</title> by ‘Abd al-Bāqī, see <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/work_7106"><idno>Persian MS
                              477</idno></ref>.</note>
                  </msItem>
